Recessed 4 in. Disinfection Module with Care222 Technology By Healthcare Lighting Overview Specifications HDMTM reduces active pathogens* on non-porous surfaces using Ushio Care222 far-UVC disinfection** technology. HDM features a mercury-free far-UVC excimer lamp that contains a patented short pass filter for narrow band 222nm emission. This removes wavelengths that penetrate the living tissue in skin or beyond the tear layer in eyes***. HDM recessed is available in a 4 inch nominal size in a round shape. Available in black, bronze, silver and white finishes. Discreet form factor seamlessly integrates into spaces and is ideal for bathrooms, counter tops and other continual-use areas. UV source emits a soft violet glow from a 1.75" x 2.25" opening when powered. LED status indicator visible from room. UV module serviceable from below. *Refer to product specification sheets at acuitybrands.com/UV-Products for efficacy claims and claim substantiation regarding specific products and pathogens **All references to disinfection are referring generally to the reduction of pathogenic bioburden and are not intended to refer to any specific definition of the term as may be used for other purposes by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration or the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency. Reduction of the pathogenic bioburden is a function of fixture run time and the distance to the UV light source, airflow, room size, shadow areas and/or other factors, and the level of reduction will vary within a specific space. This fixture is not intended for use in the cure, mitigation or prevention of disease and is not certified or approved for use as a medical device by the FDA. It is the obligation of the end-user to consult with a qualified Professional Engineer and a Certified Industrial Hygienist, if applicable, to determine whether this fixture meets the applicable requirements for system performance, code compliance, safety (including safety and hazard alerting signs), suitability and effectiveness for use in a particular application design. *** According to the International Ultraviolet Association Read More Read Less Size 5 IN Light Source UV UV Spectrum 222nm Product Type Downlight Compliance Listing BAA Regulatory Listing UL Voltage Rating 120-277 Mounting Type Recessed Series HDMR Suggested Replacement Products PRODUCT INFORMATION Spec Sheets Document Type Document Title Description Updated View Download Email Spec Sheet HDMR.pdf HDMR Recessed w Care222 Technology 5/2/2024 View Download Email Download Selected Email Selected Need to Create a Submittal Spec Sheet Take Me There Photometry & Revit (BIM) (ies) HDM Recessed .ies (BIM) HDM Recessed BIM Search within... Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications The VCVL and VCVL Ultimate (VCVLX) LEDs unite visual comfort, optical performance, and energy savings in one visually stunning package you can install anywhere. These luminaires minimize high angle glare and eliminate LED pixilation for maximum comfort. The dedicated up-light option eases contrast between the luminaire and the ceiling, creating a more visually comfortable environment. VCVL and VCVLX offer four distributions and seven lumen packages for the most complete, versatile luminaire package to illuminate the entryways, large open areas, and other common spaces in your lighting site plan. With our array of suspended and ceiling mounting options, you can illuminate any building style or architectural plan. LED Wrap By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications The Lithonia Lighting FML4W LED Wraparound provides ambient lighting for surface-mount applications. Perfect for retrofit, its wide body helps cover-up the area where a fixture is being replaced. The FML4W wrap is ideal for both residential and commercial spaces, such as laundry rooms, utility rooms, kitchens, basements, stairwells, hallways, and offices. A lumen switching option, for ALO6 models, allows adjustment from 4000 to 5000 to 6000 lumens.  Triac Dimming(TD): Wrap is 5,000 lumens at 120V only. TD is dimmable through line voltage.  ALO6: Wraps are switchable between 4,000, 5,000 and 6,000 lumens (MVOLT).  ZT: Wraps produce 5,000 lumens (MVOLT). Dimmable through 0-10V. Two ALO Packages  8,000 and 14,000 Lumens or 21,000 and 25,000 Lumens By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications When your project calls for low initial cost and high energy savings, the Lithonia Lighting ESX1 LED area luminaire delivers. ESX1 is ideal for one-for-one replacement of HID area lighting and provides up to 76% energy savings, long service life and fast payback. The ESX1 delivers 8,000 to 25,000 lumens allowing it to replace 150W to 400W HID luminaires. All ESX luminaires feature adjustable light output, providing two light levels from one product, allowing greater flexibility while helping reduce inventory costs. All luminaires feature a reversible arm that allows for mounting on both round and square poles. Three configurations of ESX1 luminaires are stocked in Acuity Brands distribution centers. The ESX1 offers a complete area lighting package and provides the combination of best product value, best price, and best delivery. Login/Register Compare Clear All Home Products ESXF1 LED Floodlight Share Email Facebook Twitter LinkedIn Pinterest Compare Share Email Facebook Twitter LinkedIn Pinterest ESXF1 LED Floodlight Adjustable + Switchable + Selectable; Replaces 75W to 150W HID By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications The Lithonia Lighting ESXF1 LED floodlight is an all-in-one flood that gives ultimate versatility by offering 36 configurations in one product. Delivering superior illumination and also offers easy access to controls for color switching, lumen switching and selectable photocell. ESXF1 comes with the two most common mountings already included in the box, making on-the-spot reconfiguring quick and easy. No more go-backs! The ESXF family has five sizes with lumen packages ranging from 1,500 to 50,000 lumens and are designed to replace 150W to 500W Quartz or 75W to 1000W HID floodlights. Suitable for both professionals and DIYers, these floodlights offer a wide flood distribution (7x7) and DLC Premium performance, making it a one-stop-shop for all floodlighting needs. Twitter LinkedIn Pinterest JEBL LED High Bay Lithonia Lighting Round LED High Bay By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications The JEBL Round LED high bay from Lithonia Lighting is built to outlast the competition. Maintaining exceptional light levels even at high ambient temperatures and able to withstand moisture, dust and airborne contaminants. The JEBL is durable, easy to install, can be used in multiple applications and saves you time and money! It's an even more affordable LED solution for users looking for a better option than the typical throw away high bay while offering an ideal one-for-one replacement of conventional HID and fluorescent high bay systems  JEBL is the one to beat! Open and Wallwash By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications LDN 4 downlights are the most cost-effective general illumination solution for commercial-grade downlight applications. The LDN4 design allows for a quiet, glare-free ceiling without compromising on efficacy. Key Features LDN Switchable (SWW) is now available with (4) Switchable CCTs options, (4) lumens packages, and multiple dimming options 55 cutoff and 75+ LPW 1.0 Spacing/Mounting Height ratio Open wallwash kicker available eldoLED drivers (10% or 1% min dimming) Available with nLight AIR capability for wireless control and connectivity Configurations support A+ Certified Solutions This product is part of the Contractor Select program. Click here for the CS product page. LDN4 is now available with SensorSwitch JOT ! Description Specification Additional information Product Downloads Connectors Hardware & Tools Description LMR-240-UF cable is an Ultra Flexible Low Loss Communications Coaxial cable, supplied in any length  manufactured by Times Microwave Systems and available from McGill Microwave  Authorised Distributor of all Times Microwave products. LMR-240-UF Background LMR-240-UF Coaxial cable is a very popular product within the Times Microwave LMR coaxial cable range. The LMR range is recognised globally as the industry standard ultra low loss, flexible, low cost, lightweight, DC  6GHz coaxial cable solution for many RF applications. This is also backed up by the best warranty and technical support in the business. Why choose LMR-240-UF LMR-240-UF has excellent reliability, unsurpassed flexibility and ultra low attenuation. The LMR-240-UF cable was designed to give more flexibility than the LMR-240 cable. It has loss figures comparable to the extremely rigid corrugated coaxial cables however manages to achieve similar flexibility to that of high loss RG Cables. LMR-240-UF is around 40% lower attenuation than competing RG Air-Dielectric type Cables. How is the LMR-240-UF low loss figures achieved This is achieved due to the cable construction specifications. The centre conductor uses a high conductivity, Bare copper stranded centre conductor. The dielectric is nitrogen injected, foamed, closed cell, Polyethylene which helps achieve 80% Velocity of Propagation. The Dielectric has a Aluminium foil outer conductor, which is chemically bonded on to it. Due to the cable construction, The attenuation is significantly lower as compared to single shielded coaxial cables. Outer Jacket All UltraFlex LMR coaxial cables comes with a TPE outer jacket. This ensures maximum flexibility for repeated or periodic flexures. Frequency Operating Band LMR-240-UF is designed to operate excellent from DC  6GHz. For any frequency band at VHF and above LMR is the obvious choice. Should you find your RF system operates at above 1GHz, LMR is once again, your best option, as RG cable typically isn t compatible with any frequency in excess of 1GHz. Applications LMR-240-UF Ultra Flexible Low Loss Communications Coaxial Cable is ideal for: Jumper Assemblies in Wireless Communications Systems Short Antenna Feeder runs WLL GPS LMR WLAN WISP WiMAX SCADA Radio antennas or receivers TVRO Mobile Antennas High gain 4G antennas Any application that requires additional flexibility Attenuation dB figures per 100m 30 MHz : 5.3dB 50 MHz : 6.8dB 150 MHz : 11.9dB 220 MHz : 14.4dB 450 MHz : 20.8dB 900 MHz : 29.8dB 1500 MHz : 38.9dB 1800 MHz : 42.8dB 2000 MHz: 45.2dB 2500 MHz: 50.9dB 5800 MHz: 80.1dB Temperature range: -400C  +850C Inner Conductor: Stranded BC (1.42mm) Dielectric: Foam PE (3.81mm) Outer conductor: Aluminium tape (3.94mm) Overall Braid: Tinned copper (4.52mm) Jacket: Black TPE (6.10mm) Mechanical Specifications Bend Radius: installation 19.1mm Bend Radius: repeated 63.5mm Bending Moment: 0.34Nm Weight lb/ft 0.05 Kg/M Tensile Strength 36.3Kg Flat Plate Crush: 0.36Kg/mm Connectors At McGill Microwave systems, we supply a huge range of connectors that include all the common interface modes. Rugged Power Supply Design Services Timing & Synchronization Services Microsemi Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of Microchip Technology Inc. (Nasdaq: MCHP), offers a comprehensive portfolio of semiconductor and system solutions for communications, defense & security, aerospace and industrial markets. Products include high-performance and radiation-hardened analog mixed-signal integrated circuits, FPGAs, SoCs and ASICs; power management products; timing and synchronization devices and precise time solutions, setting the world's standard for time; voice processing devices; RF solutions; discrete components; enterprise storage and communication solutions, security technologies and scalable anti-tamper products; Ethernet solutions; Power-over-Ethernet ICs and midspans; as well as custom design capabilities and services. Microsemi is headquartered in Aliso Viejo, California. Rugged Power Supply Design Services Timing & Synchronization Services Microsemi Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of Microchip Technology Inc. (Nasdaq: MCHP), offers a comprehensive portfolio of semiconductor and system solutions for communications, defense & security, aerospace and industrial markets. Products include high-performance and radiation-hardened analog mixed-signal integrated circuits, FPGAs, SoCs and ASICs; power management products; timing and synchronization devices and precise time solutions, setting the world's standard for time; voice processing devices; RF solutions; discrete components; enterprise storage and communication solutions, security technologies and scalable anti-tamper products; Ethernet solutions; Power-over-Ethernet ICs and midspans; as well as custom design capabilities and services. Microsemi is headquartered in Aliso Viejo, California.
